            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This has now been implemented as part of #3400 / #2903 when Python type annotations are used. When types are provided in Python syntax, we apply standard Python typing semantics that require `Optional[...]` when `None` is allowed. Since such code is either Python code or newly written Cython code, this avoids a major issue with backwards incompatibility.",
